tool_input.additional_context:
The implemented solution:
```css
/* Light mode: Use --shiki-light variables for syntax highlighting */
.astro-code.github-light span {
  color: var(--shiki-light);
}

/* Dark mode: Use --shiki-dark variables for syntax highlighting */
.dark .astro-code.github-dark-default span {
  color: var(--shiki-dark);
}
```

The HTML output confirms different syntax elements are getting different color variables:
- Keywords: `--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#FF7B72` (red)
- Functions: `--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#D2A8FF` (purple)
- Strings: `--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#A5D6FF` (blue)
- Parameters: `--shiki-light:#E36209;--shiki-dark:#FFA657` (orange)

